Detailed Description

* This program shows how HTML could be tidied directly from * a URL stream, and running on separate threads. Note the use * of the 'parse' method to parse from an InputStream, and send * the pretty-printed result to an OutputStream. * In this example thread th1 outputs XML, and thread th2 outputs * HTML. This shows that properties are per instance of Tidy.
